\begin_layout Subsection
Experimental details
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The RBF network implemented in this study was developed in ANSI C++ with the support of the open-source Armadillo library 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "armadillo"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 The optimization algorithms used were obtained from the OPTIMUS environment,
 downloaded from 
\begin_inset Flex URL
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

https://github.com/itsoulos/OPTIMUS/
\end_layout

\end_inset

(accessed on 24 June 2026)
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "optimus"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 Furthermore,
 derivative computations required by the optimization procedures were performed using the Adept automatic differentiation library 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "adept"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 To assess the performance and generalization capability of the proposed approach,
 a 10-fold cross-validation protocol was applied to all datasets.
 Each experimental setup was repeated 30 independent times,
 with a distinct initialization seed assigned to the random number generator in every run.
 Random number generation was carried out using the drand48() function provided by the C programming language.
 The average classification error is defined as:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
E_{C}\left(N\left(\overrightarrow{x},\overrightarrow{w}\right)\right)=100\times\frac{\sum_{i=1}^{N}\left(\mbox{class}\left(N\left(\overrightarrow{x_{i}},\overrightarrow{w}\right)\right)-y_{i}\right)}{N}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

The set 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 denotes the corresponding test set,
 with 
\begin_inset Formula $T=\left(x_{i},y_{i}\right),\ i=1,\ldots,N$
\end_inset

.
 Also,
 the average regression error is defined as follows:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
E_{R}\left(N\left(\overrightarrow{x},\overrightarrow{w}\right)\right)=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^{N}\left(N\left(\overrightarrow{x_{i}},\overrightarrow{w}\right)-y_{i}\right)^{2}}{N}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

