\begin_layout Subsection
Comparison with other machine learning methods
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The results of the comparative evaluation are presented in Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:experClass"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 for the classification problems and in Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:experRegression"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 for the regression problems,
 while Figures 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:classMethods"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:regressionMethods"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 display the distribution of errors via box plots and report the outcomes of the overall Friedman test.
 For classification tasks (Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:experClass"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

),
 the mean error rates were 35.18% for ADAM,
 35.50% for GRBF,
 33.25% for BFGS,
 32.16% for NEAT,
 28.68% for RBF,
 and 21.58% for the Proposed method.
 The overall Friedman test (Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:classMethods"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

) yielded 
\begin_inset Formula $p=4.5×10^{-10}$
\end_inset

,
 confirming that the differences among methods are statistically significant at a very high confidence level.
 The Proposed method achieves the lowest mean error and outperforms the second-best method,
 RBF,
 by approximately 24.8%.
 At the individual dataset level,
 the Proposed method ranked first in 26 out of 42 datasets (61.9%),
 with particularly strong performance on RING,
 SPAMBASE,
 Z_F_S,
 and ZONF_S,
 as detailed in Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:experClass"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

